This can be very easily done with XSLT. Take a look at 
<br />http://www.xml.com/pub/a/2004/05/05/tr.html 
<br />
<br />Where you can find the following transformation:
<br />
<br />&lt;!-- Copy document, stripping namespaces, i.e. for elements 
<br />
<br />     and attributes only copy the local part of their names. --&gt;
<br />
<br />&lt;xsl:stylesheet xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" version="1.0"&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;xsl:template match="*"&gt;
<br />
<br />                               &lt;xsl:element name="{local-name()}"&gt;
<br />
<br />                                               &lt;xsl:apply-templates select="@*|node()"/&gt;
<br />
<br />                               &lt;/xsl:element&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;xsl:template match="@*"&gt;
<br />
<br />                               &lt;xsl:attribute name="{local-name()}"&gt;&lt;xsl:value-of select="."/&gt;&lt;/xsl:attribute&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;xsl:template match="processing-instruction()|comment()"&gt;
<br />
<br />                               &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
<br />
<br />                                               &lt;xsl:apply-templates select="node()"/&gt;
<br />
<br />                               &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
<br />
<br />                &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
<br />
<br />&lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;
